{@--1@} A cavity
formed by folding and joining the
open hands together, the hollow of the
hands; hence, a cavity-ful of anything
(changed to {#aMjala#} or {#°li#} after {#dvi#}
and {#tri#} in {#dvigu#} <ab>comp.</ab>, <ls>P. V. 4. 102</ls>);
{#na vAryaMjalinA pibet#} <ls>Ms. 4. 63</ls>; {#supUro#} 
{#mUzikAMjaMliH#} <ls>Pt. 1. 25</ls>;  
{#araRyabIjAMjalidAnalAlitAH#} <ls>Ku. 5. 15</ls>; {#prakIrRaH puzpARAM#}
{#haricaraRayoraMjAleraMyaM#} <ls>Ve. 1. 1</ls> a 
cavityful of flowers; so {#jalasyAMjalayo daSa#}
<ls>Y. 3. 105</ls> 10 cavity-fuls or libations
of water; {#SravaRAMjalipuwapeyaM#} <ls>Ve. 1. 4</ls>
to be drunk by the cavity of the
ear; {#aMjaliM rac, baMD, kf#} or {#ADA#} fold
the hands together and raise them
to the head in supplication or 
salutation; {#badDaH kAtaryAdaraviMdakuqmalaniBo#}
{#mugDaH praRAmAMjaliH#} <ls>U. 3. 37.</ls> 
{@--2@} Hence a
mark of respect or salutation; {#kaH#}
{#SakreRa kftaM necCedaDimUrDAnamaMjalim#}  
<ls>Bk. 8. 84</ls>; {#baDyatAmaBayayAcanAMjaliH#} <ls>R. 11. 78.</ls>
{@--3@} A measure of corn = {#kuqava#}; another
measure = {#prasfta#}, or one-half of a {#mAnikA#}.

folding the hands,
respectful salutation; {#lubDamarTena#} 
{#gfhRIyAt krudDaM cAMjalikarmaRA#} <ls>Chāṇ. 33.</ls>
